Additional Job Details:&amp;nbsp;  - 10-12 years’ work experience.&amp;nbsp;   
  - 6 - 8 years Open Pages required. Certified Preferred. ---Using Version 8.02, but if someone has 7.9 experience and above would be great.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Workflows, AFCON, AURA experience.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Must be comfortable and this person will play a lead role to assist with other employees.&amp;nbsp;   
  - SDLC process and working with QA automation.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Someone with financial experience would be beneficial.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Provide OpenPages development (Trigger/Helper, Workflow, BPM, module configuration and customization).&amp;nbsp;   
  - Provide development support to the management of GRC related projects and scheduled releases.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Troubleshooting of reported issues related to developed/configured solutions.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Work with IT and business leads to understand and build development requirements and similar business analysis tasks.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Advise on possible impacts and outcomes of changes made to the IBM OpenPages solution&amp;nbsp;   
  - Ensure coordination between the Product owner and tech organizations.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Knowledge of various QA techniques/automation Tools, Defect management and prioritization&amp;nbsp;.
